The paper discusses the use of machine learning and computational intelligence techniques in analyzing Starcraft matches, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The creation and analysis of datasets also involves techniques such as data processing and pattern recognition, which are relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and game theory (cs.GT). The use of frames for temporal studies suggests the involvement of computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) techniques.
